</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR217:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR217"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              217-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 217</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Bryan<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>June 03, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to California BBQ Month. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 217, as introduced, Bryan.
                          California BBQ Month.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would proclaim the month of June as California BBQ Month, as specified.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_BAA4BB57-8030-437E-B5E3-35C1BB4F87F9"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Barbecue traditions have long served as an important part of California’s cultural heritage, bringing together families, friends, neighbors, and communities through cookouts, celebrations, festivals, and public gatherings; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3427298A-1F59-4891-A99C-EC68C5EC3D09"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California barbecue traditions have been influenced by generations of ranching, farming, outdoor cooking, and community-centered gatherings that reflect the diverse history of the state; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_39E4D354-F309-4082-A517-808D61664E5F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California’s barbecue culture has been shaped by Indigenous, Mexican, Spanish, African American, Asian American, and regional American culinary traditions that together contribute to the state’s unique food culture; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BDBEF4AE-A4F2-4F32-ACC7-8F5696B52E83"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Community cookouts and barbecue gatherings continue to foster fellowship, hospitality, cultural exchange, and neighborhood connection among Californians of all backgrounds; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C79CF26F-3845-49BC-BCE9-D1382ADA9AD0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California pitmasters, chefs, restaurateurs, food vendors, ranchers, farmers, workers, neighbors, families, and small businesses all play an important role in preserving barbecue traditions, supporting local economies, fostering culinary innovation, and strengthening community connections across the state; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_33A86830-0ACD-45FA-B634-49944807B4E3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California’s barbecue traditions contribute to local economies by supporting restaurants, food vendors, tourism, hospitality, agriculture, and community events throughout the state; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_DF2D236A-7E0A-4501-9D3F-4B3FF415C826"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The recognition of California BBQ Month provides an opportunity to celebrate the individuals, businesses, workers, and communities that help sustain and advance barbecue traditions throughout California; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E44D1D3E-E9CE-4353-A913-B3DE93F10807"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature proclaims the month of June as California BBQ Month; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_3CD59E2C-A27A-4F97-AC0C-AEB24319D561"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature encourages Californians to celebrate California BBQ Month by supporting local barbecue establishments, participating in cookouts and community gatherings, and recognizing the cultural and historical significance of barbecue traditions throughout the state; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E52B317D-E3A1-4C97-BE90-5F76512143E4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature recognizes and celebrates the contributions of California pitmasters, chefs, restaurateurs, workers, ranchers, farmers, food vendors, neighbors, families, and small businesses that help sustain and advance barbecue traditions throughout the state; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_2C11B894-4E39-4173-9F58-250CFF701869"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
